    {
      "id": "ae1295fc287315215c952adaa4e6097186240deb",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 109,
        "name": "Christopher J. Morrone",
        "email": "morrone2@llnl.gov",
        "username": "morrone"
      },
      "date": "2017-03-17 20:37:15.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\nI don't think that this is the proper use of the package name \"lustre-devel\".  Granted, there was a \"lustre-devel\" in the past, but it wasn't doing the right thing either.\n\nIf we were to have a lustre-devel package, it should only contain things like lustreapi.h, liblustreapi.so, etc.  It should only contain those interfaces that we've explicitly decided are external programming interfaces.  Exposing lustre's internal-use-only header files is not the correct thing to include in lustre-devel.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "c7f674f7e4882092cae9131f0ba668e51bd20c4c",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 109,
        "name": "Christopher J. Morrone",
        "email": "morrone2@llnl.gov",
        "username": "morrone"
      },
      "date": "2017-03-17 20:38:26.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nSorry, I was thinking of \"lustre-source\" in the past, not a lustre-devel in the past.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
